      "question": "A box contains $40$ cards numbered from $1$ to $40$. If a card is drawn at random from the box, find the probability that the number on the card is a multiple of $5$.",
      "answer": "$1/5$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the total number of possible outcomes, which is the total count of cards, $n(S) = 40$.",
          "Identify the favourable outcomes which are multiples of $5$ between $1$ and $40$, i.e., $\\{5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30, 35, 40\\}$.",
          "Count the favourable outcomes, $n(E) = 8$.",
          "Calculate the probability using $P(E) = \\frac{n(E)}{n(S)} = \\frac{8}{40} = \\frac{1}{5}$."
        ],
        "derivation": "n(S) = 40 \\\\ E = \\{5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30, 35, 40\\} \\\\ n(E) = 8 \\\\ P(E) = \\frac{n(E)}{n(S)} = \\frac{8}{40} = \\frac{1}{5}"
      },
